#~ msgid ""
#~ "In addition to providing built-in [authentication](/docs/{{version}}/"
#~ "authentication) services, Laravel also provides a simple way to authorize "
#~ "user actions against a given resource. For example, even though a user is "
#~ "authenticated, they may not be authorized to update or delete certain "
